🍫 HOSTESS/LITTLE DEBBIE CUPCAKES 🎂

Our next childhood throwback recipe is the famous Hostess/Little Debbie creme filled chocolate cupcakes. Who remembers and how did we do? 🔥

Cupcakes:
1 cup all purpose flour
1/2 cup cake flour
1/2 cup cocoa powder
3/4 cup sugar 
1 egg
1/2 cup vegetable oil
1/2 cup milk
1/2 cup hot water 
1/2 tsp salt 
1 tsp vanilla
1 tsp baking soda 

Marshmallow filling:
1/2 cup heavy cream 
1/2 cup marshmallow creme or fluff 

Ganache: 
1/4 cup heavy cream 
1/4-1/2 cup chocolate chips 

Icing:
1/2 cup powdered sugar
1 tbsp heavy cream 

Preheat your oven to 310F. In a large mixing bowl, combine the milk, vegetable oil, egg, sugar, vanilla, and hot water. Sift in the two types of flours, salt, baking soda and cocoa powder. Mix until smooth. Fill your cupcake tins about halfway. Bake for 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean. Allow to cool down. Make the filling by whipping the heavy cream until stiff peaks form then add the marshmallow creme in and whisk until combined. Pour into a piping bag or ziplock bag. Core the center of your cupcakes leaving a small space of cupcake at the bottom. Fill the hole with the marshmallow filling and top with the removed cupcake piece. Make your ganache by microwaving for about 30 seconds the heavy cream and chocolate chips. Dip the cupcakes into the ganache and allow to dry or (pop in the freezer for 10 min). Make your icing by combining the two ingredients and design the top of your cupcakes in “loops”. ....ENJOY! 😍
.
.
.
.

node.text:
🌈 FUNFETTI BLONDIES 🔥 

Working on so many new recipes to share very soon, here’s a sneak peek! 

1/2 cup chopped white chocolate 
1/3 cup sprinkles 
1 cup flour 
1/2 cup butter 
1/2 cup brown sugar 
1/4 cup white sugar 
1/2 tsp salt 
1/2 tsp baking powder 
1 tsp vanilla 
2 eggs 

Preheat oven to 350F. Microwave butter until partially melted in a large bowl. Add the sugars and vanilla then mix. Add the eggs and mix again. Fold in the flour, baking powder and salt until combined. Add the chopped white chocolate and sprinkles. Mix until incorporated and pour the mixture into a 8x8 pan lined with parchment paper. Bake for 28-30 minutes and allow to cool completely before removing from the pan ✨
.
.
.
.

🍫OREO CHEESECAKE SLU*TY BROWNIES 🔥

Brownie layer:
1/3 cup heavy cream
1 cup chocolate chips 
4 tbsp butter
2 eggs
1/3 cup sugar
1/4 cup cocoa powder 
1/2 cup flour

Cheesecake layer: 
1/3 cup heavy cream 
6oz cream cheese 
1/3 cup sugar 
1 tsp vanilla 
1 egg 
Crushed Oreos 

Cookie layer:
1/2 cup salted butter 
1/2 cup brown sugar 
1/4 cup white sugar 
1 tsp vanilla
1 egg 
1 cup cake flour 
1/2 tsp baking soda 
1 cup chocolate chips 

Combine all ingredients for each layer separately. In pan lined with parchment paper, add the brownie mixture. Top with a layer of Oreos. Add the cheesecake layer and then the cookie layer. Bake on 350F for 45-50 minutes or until done in the center! 
.
.
.
.

🍪AHOY MATES! 🥤 

@wawa X @chipsahoy have launched limited time offers such as the vanilla CHIPS AHOY! Cream Smoothie & the Caramel CHIPS AHOY! Frozen Cappuccino with CHIPS AHOY! Cookie Pieces in each 😍. #sponsored 

We’re giving away a $10 @wawa gift card to celebrate the launch. To enter: 

1. Like this post
2. Follow @wawa 
3. Tag 2 friends in the comments below using #chipsahoyxwawa and #giveaway 

Winner will be announced via stories on 7/26 ….GOOD LUCK! ✨

All of the limited time offers come in vanilla, chocolate or caramel including the not pictured Cheesecake Smoothie, Milkshake, Flurricane, and Sundae. #chipsahoyxwawa #wawa #wawarun https://bit.ly/ChipsahoyxWawa

💙 BLUE OREO CREPE 🫓

1 cup flour ⁣
3 tbsp melted butter ⁣
3/4 cup milk⁣
1/2 cup water⁣
2 tbsp sugar ⁣
1 1/2 tsp vanilla ⁣
2 eggs⁣
1/4 cup crushed oreo 
2 tbsp nutella 
⁣
⁣
Combine all of the base ingredients into a bowl and whisk until well mixed. Allow batter to stand for 5 minutes then add the crushed Oreo cookies to the mixture. Pour 1/2 cup of batter into your crepe maker (or skillet) and spread using a wooden spreader. Allow to cook for about 1-2 minutes until firm.  Fold in half and add your Nutella and crushed Oreos then fold again. Top however you wish ✨🥰⁣
.
.
.
.

🍫NUTELLA OREO POPTARTS🫓

1 roll refrigerated pie crust 
3 heaping spoons of nutella 
1 egg beaten 
Crushed Oreos 

Nutella ganache: 
2 tbsp Nutella 
Splashes of heavy cream 

Preheat oven to 350F. Roll out the pie crust then cut along the edges to make a single square. Cut the square in half and then cut each half into three. You should have 6 squares total by now. Add a heaping dollop of Nutella to 3 of the squares and spread it out leaving the edge free of Nutella. Sprinkle crushed Oreo on top of the Nutella. Place the remaining three squares on top of each of the squares with Nutella. Press the edges down with a fork. Brush the beaten egg on the 3 poptarts and bake for 15 minutes. While the poptarts bake, microwave 1/8 cup of heavy cream until hot and add two tbsp Nutella to a small bowl. Pour the warm heavy cream over the Nutella in splashes mixing until desired consistency. Allow the poptarts to cool 10 minutes then top with the Nutella ganache. 
.
.
.
.

🇨🇺CUBAN ESPRESSO BROWNIES 🍫

This video is from one of our collabs with the amazing @cafelallave. A delicious Cuban coffee brand. While what is happening is Cuba is nothing new, they really need ALL OF OUR support more than ever right now. As a Social Worker, my heart hurts. My heart hurts for that these people have had to endure for all these years. My heart hurts for the lack of dignity and respect they deserve. We need to show we stand with the people of Cuba. However that may look. Maybe it’s sharing their stories, amplifying their voices, supporting Cuban brands/businesses. This morning we grabbed @vickybakery instead of our usual morning spot. At the end of the day, some support is better than NO support. 

This doesn’t have to be about politics, this HAS to be about humanity. We need to educate ourselves if we aren’t familiar with the situation. There are some great tools out there circulating that explain exactly what is happening & why it’s happening. There are also some great initiatives to help people in Cuba as much as we can from the outside. I’ll share all of this in my stories if you wish to learn more.  In the meantime, #soscuba 🇨🇺 !!! Song is called “Libre” which means free (because that’s what the people of Cuba want to be) -by @iksonmusic #cubalibre #cuba #patriayvida #cubanamericans #libertad #freedom
